=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect aniline by acetylation (Ac2O or CH3COCl, base) to give acetanilide, PhNHCOCH3. | Step 2: Nitrate acetanilide (HNO3/H2SO4, 0–5 °C) to form mainly p-nitroacetanilide; hydrolyze the amide (H3O+, heat or NaOH/H2O then acid workup) to give p-nitroaniline, O2N–C6H4–NH2. | Step 3: Diazotize p-nitroaniline with NaNO2/HCl at 0–5 °C to generate p-nitrobenzenediazonium chloride, O2N–C6H4–N2+Cl−. | Step 4: Dissolve salicylic acid in NaOH/Na2CO3 to form sodium salicylate/phenoxide, then couple with the cold p-nitrobenzenediazonium salt at the activated 5-position of the salicylate ring to give the azo-coupled sodium salt. | Step 5: Acidify the reaction mixture to obtain alizarin yellow R (5-(4-nitrophenylazo)salicylic acid), O=C(O)c2cc(N=Nc1ccc(N(=O)=O)cc1)ccc2O.

